<p><b>Torture;  Violence 
</b></p>
<p><b>against women;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged sentencing to death by stoning for adultery. According to information 
received, on May 13 2012, the criminal court of Ombada in Khartoum, central 
Sudan, sentenced Ms. Intisar Sharif Abdallah, 20 years old and mother of 
three children, to death by stoning based on charges of adultery, under article 
146 of Sudan&#8216;s criminal code of 1991. It is reported that although she had 
</p>
<p>initially pleaded not guilty, she admitted to the charges at a later hearing, after 
reportedly being beaten by her brother. The conviction was based solely on 
this testimony.  It is reported that during the trial, Ms. Sharif Abdallah did not 
have access to a lawyer, nor an interpreter, despite the fact that she has a 
limited knowledge of Arabic, while the man co-accused of the same charges 
was simply released after denying them. Ms. Sharif Abdallah is reportedly 
being detained with her youngest son, who is four months old, while her two 
other children are in the care of her family. 
</p>
