<p>Alleged killing of a LGBTI rights defender. According to the information 
received, on 9 June 2012, two unidentified men followed Mr. Thapelo 
Makhutle to his home in Kuruman, in the John Taolo Gaetsewe district, 
Northern Cape province. This occurred shortly after an argument between 
them on Thapelo Makhutle's sexuality. Mr. Makhutle. was reportedly a 
member of LEGBO, an advocacy group based in Northern Cape which 
provides support and training to rural LGBTI communities. Mr. Makhutle 
actively spoke out against LGBTI discrimination and conducted workshops 
with LGBTI youth on human rights, HIV and AIDS and other social issues. 
The same day, his body was found on his bed, with the throat cut.   
