<p>LKA 3/2012 
<b>Sri Lanka  
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Freedom of religion;   
</b></p>
<p> 
Alleged assault by a Buddhist Monk teacher of a student in the Kandy 
District. According to the information received, Mr. X, a 14 year-old student 
at Mahanama College Geatam was assaulted by his teacher, Mr. Y, when he 
refused to learn Buddhism after stating that he is a Catholic. Mr. X was 
allegedly assaulted until his left ear started bleeding and was left without 
recourse to any medical treatment and told not to tell anyone about the 
assault. Mr. X reportedly became ill and was hospitalized in the following 
days. His father, Mr. Z, filed a complaint with the Kandy Police (WCIB 
1/84/16) despite threats of violence from Mr. Y.  
</p>
