afterwards made public and widely distributed among social media. It is 
reported that Ms. Najiba was married to a Taliban member, and was accused 
of committing adultery with a Taliban commander. It was also reported that 
on 13 July 2012, Ms. Hanifa Safi, a regional representative of the Afghan 
Ministry of Women Affairs in Laghman province, and her husband were 
killed while driving through the provincial capital, Mehtar Lam, when a bomb 
allegedly attached to their car exploded. Ms. Safi was reportedly the second 
provincial head of women&#8216;s affairs to be assassinated since these posts were 
</p>
