<p><b>Summary executions;   
</b></p>
<p> 
Alleged imposition of the death penalty on two individuals with psychosocial 
disabilities. According to the information received, Messrs. Marcus Ray 
Tyrone Druery and Daniel Wayne Cook were convicted of murder and 
sentenced to death in Texas and Arizona, respectively. In both cases, evidence 
points to the conclusion that they suffer from psychosocial disabilities. Mr. 
Druery&#8216;s execution was scheduled to take place on 1 August 2012, and the 
</p>
<p>execution of Mr. Cook on 8 August 2012.  
