<p>Alleged torture and risk of imminent execution of five representatives of the 
Ahwazi Arab minority. According to the information received, Messrs. 
Mohammad Ali Amouri, Sayed Jaber Alboshoka, Sayed Mokhtar Alboshoka,  
Hashem Sha&#8216;bani Amouri, and Hadi Rashidi (or Rashedi), all representatives 
</p>
<p>of the Ahwazi Arab minority in the Islamic Republic of Iran, have been 
sentenced to death for terrorism-related charges, including moharebeh 
(&#8213;enmity against God&#8214;), efsad-e fel arz (&#8213;sowing corruption on earth&#8214;), 
&#8213;gathering and colluding against State security&#8214; and &#8213;spreading propaganda 
</p>
<p>against the system&#8214;, which are not considered as most serious crimes under 
</p>
<p>international law. Following a trial that allegedly did not comply with 
international human rights law provisions of fair trial and due process, they 
are reported to be at risk of imminent execution. It is further alleged that they 
have been subjected to torture or ill-treatment.   
