<p><b>Torture;   
</b></p>
<p> 
Alleged mistreatment by the US Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA). 
According to information received, on 21 April 2012, Mr. Daniel Chong, a 23 
year old University of California San Diego student, was detained following a 
drug raid on the apartment in which Mr. Chong was smoking marijuana. At 
the local DEA field office in San Diego, California, he was then reportedly 
placed in a five-foot by ten-foot windowless holding cell, handcuffed and left 
for five days without access to food, water, or restroom facilities. 
</p>
