</p>
<p>Allegation that a draft decree on &#8213;management, provision and use of internet 
services and information on the network&#8214; would run contrary to the right to 
</p>
<p>freedom of expression. According to information received, the draft decree 
contains provisions which would run contrary to the right to freedom of 
expression, in particular provisions prohibiting the use of Internet for certain 
purposes, dealing with the responsibility of Internet service providers and 
other intermediaries, and requiring that Internet service providers should filter 
information. In addition, the draft decree would require Internet users to use 
their real name when posting information. 
