<p>Alleged denial of access to medical treatment to a pastor in Ghezal Hesar 
Prison. According to the information received, Pastor Benham Irani was 
arrested on 31 May 2011, and transferred to Ghezal Hesar Prison where he is 
currently serving his sentences. Pastor Behnam Irani has allegedly been 
denied hospital treatment for severe bleeding due to stomach ulcers and 
complications with his colon that have caused him to lose consciousness 
temporarily. It was reported that Pastor Irani has received death threats from 
fellow prisoners and sustained regular beatings from his cell mates and prison 
authorities. It is reported that as a result of injuries sustained during these 
assaults, he has difficulty walking. Pastor Irani also has problem with his 
vision and is in poor health. Pastor Irani was the subject of previous 
communications (see A/HRC/18/51, IRN 4/2011).  
