<p>KEN 3/2012 
<b>Kenya  
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Freedom of peaceful 
</b></p>
<p><b>assembly and of 
</b></p>
<p><b>association;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Allegation relating to a Court&#8216;s decision impacting on the enjoyment of the 
right to freedom of association. According to the information received, on 25 
July 2012, the High Court of Mombasa ruled, in a judgment Randu Nzai 
Ruwa &amp; 2 Others v Internal Security Minister &amp; Another Miscellaneous, that 
the decision that had banned the Mombasa Republican Council, a political 
group advocating secession, was unconstitutional. This judgment is reportedly 
instrumental in advancing a better understanding of freedom of association in 
Kenya. In this letter, the Special Rapporteur makes reference to his thematic 
report about best practices related to freedom of association and of peaceful 
assembly, and notably reminds that the right to freedom of association shall 
also apply to unregistered groups. 
</p>
<p> 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
