received an anonymous telephone threat. On 19 July, the group's offices were 
ransacked, during which confidential and sensitive documentation concerning 
psychological care given to victims of torture was reportedly stolen. It is 
alleged that other files were overturned, a computer was turned on and more 
than R$1,500 in cash was stolen. Founded in 1985, GTNM/RJ supports 
former victims of torture and works for the full implementation of the 
National Truth Commission by campaigning for the opening of State archives 
from the period of the military dictatorship. 
