<p>Allegations of disproportionate use of force during demonstrations, resulting 
in the death of two protesters. According to the information received, on 9 
July 2012, in Qatif Province, a demonstration organized in response to the 
arrest of a prominent Shiite activist, Sheikh Nimr Baqr al-Nimr, was met with 
excessive use of force by law enforcement officials resulting in the death of 
protesters Mr. Akbar al-Shakuri and Mr. Mohammed al-Filfil. A number of 
participants were also arrested and charged with illegal gathering. On 25 July 
2012, hundreds of people gathered in Jeddah to protest against the detention 
of their relatives, but the police used tear gas bombs, rubber and live bullets to 
disperse the protesters injuring dozens of them. Around 14 protesters were 
reportedly arrested, including seven children. Amongst those arrested was Mr. 
Mohamed Al Shakoury, whose brother was killed during the 9 July 
demonstrations. 
