<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Summary executions;   
</b></p>
<p> 
Alleged imposition of the death penalty on a man suffering from psychosocial 
disabilities. According to the information received, Mr. Terrance Williams, a 
46-year-old African American man, has been sentenced to death for a murder 
committed in 1984 when he was 18 years old. The victim, who had allegedly 
abused him during several years, was beaten to death. Moreover, Mr. 
Williams was also found guilty in a separate trial of third-degree murder, 
which does not carry the death penalty, for the killing of a 51-yers old man 
and an armed robbery when he was 16 years old. It has been reported that Mr 
Williams was physically abused by his mother and stepfather. Moreover, he 
was a victim of rape and sexual assault. According to the allegations received, 
he has been diagnosed with Post-traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD). A clinical 
psychologist has underlined that the violence and abuse of Mr. Williams was 
so severe in his childhood that he suffers from severe and long lasting 
psychological damage.  
