<p>JOR 2/2012 
<b>Jordan  
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Disappearances;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Torture;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged forcible return to Jordan and imminent threat of torture. According to 
the information received, Mr. Ashraf Mohammad Yousef Abdulsalam was 
arrested and tortured at the GID headquarters in Amman, Jordan in 2010. He 
later joined his family and took residence in Bahrain. On 25 September 2012, 
he was arrested in Bahrain and allegedly forcibly returned to Jordan without 
further information being provided to his family on his fate or whereabouts in 
spite of requests thereof.   
</p>
<p>18/01/2013 
 
 
