<p><b>Myanmar;  Violence 
</b></p>
<p><b>against women;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Follow up to the 30 December 2011 communication (A/HRC/20/30, MMR 
5/2011) regarding the alleged abduction and rape of Ms. Sumlut Roi Ja by 
military personnel attached to Light Infantry Battalion 321, Mu Bum frontline 
post in Momouk district, Kachin state, and the alleged detention and sexual 
assault of three other women at the same military post.  The Government of 
Myanmar&#8216;s 22 March 2012 reply to the 30 December communication stated 
that the authorities concerned, including military and civil officials, had 
conducted an initial investigation into the case and that further investigations 
were being pursued to produce more concrete results. This communication 
asks for an update on the results of these further investigations to enable the 
mandate holders to ascertain the facts regarding the allegations contained in 
the 30 December communication and to ascertain the current situation of the 
alleged victims. 
