<p><b>Adequate housing;   
</b></p>
<p> 
Alleged imminent eviction of 62 families (160 persons) living in house 15, 
building 2, Ilyushina street, Saint Petersburg. According to information 
received, the tenants of the above mentioned building were employees of the 
State owned Lenstroykorporazia construction company and were allocated 
housing in the building in 1991, as state employees. Reportedly, the building 
was privatized in 1995 and registered as the property of the Chetverty Trest 
company. According to information received, the existing tenants were not 
accorded any tenure rights during the privatization process, and are currently 
under threat of eviction by the registered private owner. 
