</b></p>
<p><b>lawyers;  Torture;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged arrest and detention of lawyer and human rights activist. According to the 
information received, Ms. Nasrin Sotoudeh, a lawyer and prominent human rights 
activist, had been held in solitary confinement since her arrest on 4 September 
</p><p>2010. She reportedly resumed her hunger strike on 4 December 2010. On 17 
December, she was reportedly transferred to the clinic of Evin prison in a critical 
condition. Ms. Sotoudeh was the subject of an earlier communication (see 
A/HRC/16/44/Add.1, para 1272). 
</p>
<p>28/11/2012 
 
 
 
