<p><b>Torture;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged death in custody due to torture by prison guards.  According to the 
information received, on 7 February 2012, Mr. Ahmed Ramzy Ali Amar, aged 27, 
who was serving his sentence at New Valley Prison, was beaten by prison guards 
following a dispute with one of the guards who came to search his cell. 
Subsequently, he was taken to a solitary confinement cell as punishment. He was 
pronounced dead two days later by prison security, who claimed that he had 
committed suicide, while his former cellmates reportedly saw marks of severe 
torture on his body. 
</p>
